1/ $index is a way to show which iteration of a loop you’re in. If we set up an ng-repeat to repeat over the letters in ‘somewords’, like so:

<div ng-app="app">
  <div ng-repeat="item in 'somewords'.split('')">
    {{$index + 1}}. {{item}}
  </div>
</div>

Implement Doc: https://thinkster.io/egghead/index-event-log

